.TH LLMESH\-CLIENT 1 "April 2026" "llmesh" "llmesh Manual"
.SH NAME
llmesh\-client \- connect a local llama.cpp server to the llmesh router
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B llmesh\-client
[\fB\-config\fR\ \fIpath\fR]
[\fB\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B llmesh\-client
is the worker component of the llmesh system.
It establishes a persistent WebSocket connection to an llmesh router,
advertises the models the local
.B llama.cpp
server supports,
and processes inference jobs dispatched by the router.
.PP
Streaming token deltas are forwarded back to the router in real time,
which proxies them to the waiting HTTP caller.
.PP
On disconnect the client reconnects automatically using exponential back\-off:
1\ s, 2\ s, 4\ s, 8\ s, 16\ s, 32\ s, 60\ s maximum.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-config " path"
Path to the YAML configuration file.
Defaults to
.IR /config.yaml .
.TP
.B \-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is a YAML document.
A minimal example:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
router_url: "wss://llm.example.com/ws/client"
router_token: "ct-alice-a1b2c3d4e5f6g7h8"
models:
  - endpoint: "http://localhost:8080"
.fi
.RE
.SS Fields
.TP
.B router_url
WebSocket URL of the llmesh router.
Use
.B wss://
for TLS-encrypted connections (recommended in production) or
.B ws://
for unencrypted local connections.
The path component must be
.IR /ws/client .
.TP
.B router_token
Client token created via the router admin UI (Client Tokens page).
Tokens begin with
.IR ct\- .
This value authenticates this client instance to the router.
Keep it secret; it grants the ability to receive and process jobs.
.TP
.B max_concurrent
Maximum number of inference requests this client processes simultaneously.
Optional.
When omitted (or set to zero) the limit is auto-detected from the slot count
.RB ( total_slots )
reported by the llama.cpp server, falling back to
.B 1
if the server does not advertise one.
Set an explicit positive integer to override.
.TP
.B models
List of model definitions.
Each entry maps a llama.cpp endpoint to the model name callers will use.
.RS
.TP
.B name
Model identifier as sent by API callers in the
.I model
field of their request (e.g.\~\fIllama3.2:3b\fR).
Optional.
When omitted, the client auto-detects the name from the endpoint's
.I /v1/models
response when it connects.
The router matches this name exactly when selecting a client for a job.
.TP
.B endpoint
Base URL of the
.B llama.cpp
HTTP server for this model (e.g.\~\fIhttp://localhost:8080\fR).
The client appends
.I /v1/chat/completions
when forwarding jobs.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Run with a custom config file
.nf
llmesh\-client \-config /etc/llmesh/client.yaml
.fi
.SS Run inside Docker (recommended)
Download
.I docker-compose.client.yml
and
.I config.yaml.example
from the router admin UI (Docs \(-> Client files), rename the example to
.IR config.yaml ,
fill in your token, then:
.nf
docker compose \-f docker\-compose.client.yml up \-d
.fi
.SS Run directly on the host
Start llama.cpp on port 8080:
.nf
llama\-server \-m ./models/llama3.2\-3b.gguf \-\-port 8080
.fi
Start the client:
.nf
llmesh\-client \-config ./config.yaml
.fi
.SS Multiple models on one host
Run a separate llama.cpp instance on a distinct port for each model:
.nf
# Terminal 1
llama\-server \-m llama3.2\-3b.gguf \-\-port 8080
# Terminal 2
llama\-server \-m mistral\-7b.gguf \-\-port 8081
.fi
Configure both in
.IR config.yaml :
.nf
models:
  - name: "llama3.2:3b"
    endpoint: "http://localhost:8080"
  - name: "mistral\-7b"
    endpoint: "http://localhost:8081"
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /config.yaml
Default configuration file path (inside the Docker container).
On the host, pass an explicit path with
.BR \-config .
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
The client logs to standard output in the following format:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
2026/04/16 12:00:00 llmesh\-client starting, router=wss://... models=2 max_concurrent=4
2026/04/16 12:00:01 ws: connected
2026/04/16 12:00:01 ws: registered 2 model(s)
.fi
.RE
.PP
A persistent
.I "dial failed"
message indicates a network or authentication problem \(em verify the router URL
and token, and check that the router is reachable from this host.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Clean shutdown (SIGINT / SIGTERM).
.TP
.B 1
Fatal error: bad configuration, missing required fields, or unrecoverable startup failure.
.SH SEE ALSO
.B llama\-server(1)
.PP
llama.cpp project:
.I https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp
